cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
1) cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with joint source-channel coding and proposes a new approach to address the weakness of the conventional approach. 
2) cs.MM (Multimedia) is also likely as the paper focuses on the transmission of digital images. 
3) cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is another possible category as the paper deals with digital image transmission and processing. 
4) cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper mentions the use of iterative Belief Propagation for decoding. 
5) cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a less likely category, but possible as the paper discusses the building blocks of source coders and proposes a new approach for entropy coding.
